* Task 5 fixture: PERFORM without inline definition
* Same as 04-perform-inline-and-external.NSP but WITHOUT the DEFINE SUBROUTINE.
* Proves that the inline-marking behavior is data-driven: removing the definition
* marks the same SHARED-LOGIC target as unresolved (left for external resolution).

DEFINE DATA
LOCAL
  1 STATUS-CODE (N2)
END DEFINE

PERFORM SHARED-LOGIC

MOVE 1 TO STATUS-CODE

PERFORM EXTERNAL-ONLY

WRITE 'Done'

END
